1) option : -sn
  usage   : scans ports and checks wether they are alive
  working  : sends ICMP echo requests , TCP SYN to port 443 and TCP ACK to ports
              returns a list of available IPs and MAC addresses
  example : nmap -sn

NOTE:- ICMP Internet Control Message Protocol, are you there? messages


2) option :  -Pn
  working   : evades windows firewalls to send ICMP messages . Skips host discovery and jumps
            to port scanning. Also known as ping sweep
  usage   : use when you know server exists and isn't showing normally
